annotation.TEXT: But now, is there a safe place for me to land? ...Yep.
OH, NOOO!!!
Good thing I wasn't standing on the left side of the platform when that blue guy there respawned!
Hmm... I probably could've made it over the pipe from there. Well, whatever.
With this being Sky World, it's not surprising that there's a lot of platforming to do here.
HARRY UP!
I saw stuff up there, but I can't reach it from here. Maybe I'll be making my way up there from another direction, or maybe I'll get a broom at some point to fly up there with.
Whoa, boy. That could've been almost dangerous.
I saw stars and I think a pipe up there in the upper-right. I'll probably get to them later.
Not quite enough running room to take flight from that cloud. Also, I'd better be careful not to get hit by a random blue FOE in a random spot while I'm flying/floating around...
Oh, wait. Maybe I shouldn't kill them all.
Whoa. Those yellow guys can be surprisingly dangerous. If you go high enough to spawn them, but then drop back down without killing them, be careful.
I didn't do that here, but I pulled it off on a couple of my other failed attempts. However, I have to go the long way here for these stars anyway, so whatever.
Okay, I can bounce off of them repeatedly with normal stomps, and I can kill them with a drill stomp.
Okay, let's not miss with a drill stomp again. I can't expect a miracle to occur every time I screw up!
I've gotta keep in mind the momentum that I can get from jumping off of a moving platform.
Oh, man. New world music, and a new enemy! It looks like it behaves like the larger Raven enemies from Yoshi's Island.
Yep! I think I had to time my broom hovering really well to make it, but I pulled it off!
Hello, and welcome back to Super Marisa World! Last time, I defeated Letty, and 100%-ed all of world 1...
Okay, it took me several attempts to find those blasted stars, and here's where they were...
Woo, barely made it. You do indeed have to time your broom hovering just right.
To be continued... Ze!
Ooh, a broom! And, this pipe goes somewhere.
Oh... my... pudding... Okay, that's a miracle if I ever saw one! What are the odds that I'd screw up a drill stomp in the exact spot where a hidden cloud with stars was below?
Okay, that was certainly an A+ performance, but it's not quite good enough. I want that perfect score!
Whoops. I drilled away more bricks than I wanted to there. I can still work with this, though.
The miko suit is handy for dealing with enemies along the way until I reach the broom. The Raven FOEs can be killed with "hammer" orbs.
Aha!
Yeah, I probably should kill those guys if I can, so that they won't pester me anymore.
And that's it! World 2-1-1 is now 100% cleared!
...What...
Getting back to familiar ground after getting them is indeed very tricky, and I've failed that a couple times. They're definitely the hardest stars to safely retrieve in this level.
Maybe the missing stars are back towards the beginning, like maybe way above where I started. Well, wherever they are, I'd better find them soon!
Next time, I'll be taking on 2-1-2. I wonder what tricky kinds of platforming that level will have me going through...
And now, I just have to do the rest of the platforming here without screwing up. Should be easy enough, right?
Nearly there! The last two stars are in sight!
Okay, got those stars. I was hoping to land on the pipe there, but whatever. I'll just fly up again.
Whoa! Well, I found the secret exit! I wasn't even aware that there was a secret exit in this level! (However, I would've known upon seeing the "N" if I got the normal exit first.)
Why did I do that? That could've been almost dangerous!
It's also possible to bounce off of the yellow guys up here while they're jumping to shortcut to the checkpoint, which is helpful for getting to the broom sooner, I guess.
10 attempts later...
Well, there's the goal, but I'm still 4 stars short. Since I miraculously haven't died yet, I'm going to go back and see if I can find those missing 4 stars.
But, now where do I go? Maybe I can get back to familiar territory to the left?
Ah, so there is a pipe, along with a P block. Too bad there's a wall in my way.
I wonder if there are any stars above those Raven FOEs...
Pfft. That drill stomp attempt didn't quite work since the game thought I hit the platform before the enemy, so I normal stomped him instead.
Semi-blind jump! Not quite as blind some others I've faced, though.
I see stars over there...
Still no sign of those missing 4 stars though... Well, I don't want to risk a time up, so I'll just take the secret exit now, and maybe I'll find those 4 stars on my next attempt...
Yes, they can and will drop down suddenly onto the right side of the clouds down here, so don't linger around there or you might get a sudden headache!
I can do better than that.
Whoa, geez!
And, the floating blue FOEs can be killed with either type of orb, which is really nice.
Aw, flying from down there doesn't quite take me to the yellow FOE cloud.
Ah, and I'm back in familiar territory. Okay, if I take off from where the checkpoint was, can I reach those stars?
Whoa, that was scary. Also, a yellow guy made his way down here.
Yeah, directly under the starting point. Argh, if only I had known, I could've perfected this level on my first try! Also, these P blocks contain one miko suit and 5 FOEs.
Nice, got all 8 of those in one shot!
Just some more pure platforming here.
Okay, I really hope I don't waste this miracle! Man, I might've had a hard time finding those 3 stars if I hadn't fallen right there! And to land exactly on the cloud too... Wow...
Yep. Nothing's stopping me from going above the pipe here.
But, don't get too careless when trying to do so, of course.
Yeah, this pipe down here isn't two-way, so I need to bounce off of these duders to reach the upper ledge. Otherwise, I think I could get stuck in an unwinnable situation.
That's a lot of blue FOEs in a row there.
Oh, I remember that pipe. Wow, if you just wanted to make a beeline for the goal after getting the broom, it'd probably be really easy to.
If you come down here without a broom, you will absolutely need to bounce off of one of the FOEs to escape, so don't just recklessly kill them all right away.
Stupid blue FOE. It's okay, as I can get another broom right here, and I can keep using the pipe to refresh the broom if needed.
Next order of business: Getting those 3 stars I miraculously found the first time.
I must be getting close to the end now.
That wall continues stretching up, so I guess I'll be going left here.
And, as you saw there, I had two @ symbols next to my file's score! Can I manage to add a third? Well, it'll depend on if I can perfect all of world 2! So, let's start 2-1-1!
More platforming, with potentially annoying blue FOEs floating around. I'll try to kill them if given the opportunity.
Now, I remember there being a set of stars under the pipe here, and I'm pretty sure I'll want to fly to get them.
There's a checkpoint, and I think that's the top of the wall right there. So, if I just simply drop down next to the wall on its right side...
I'm guessing that one of these was the moving green platform I saw from below earlier.
That works. However, before I break that last brick, I want to check something...
